com.rawva.structures.graphs

Interface WeightedGraph<V,W>

  • Type Parameters:
    V - the type of elements (vertices) in this graph
    W - the type of edge weights in this graph
    All Superinterfaces:
    Graph<V>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    WeightedHashGraph

    public interface WeightedGraph<V,W>
extends Graph<V>
    A weighted graph is a type of graph in which weights are associated with edges. An edge weight is an object that indicates some value associated with an edge.
    Author:
    Raymond Tang

    • Method Detail

      • addEdge

        boolean addEdge(V tail,
                V head,
                W weight)
        Adds an edge with the specified weight from the specified tail element to the specified head element. Returns true if the edge was successfully added to this graph after this call.
        Parameters:
        tail - the tail vertex
        head - the head vertex
        weight - the weight of the edge
        Returns:
        true if the edge was added to this graph after this call, else false
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if one or more of the arguments are null and this graph does not permit null values
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if some property of one or more of the arguments prevents the edge from being added to this graph
        java.lang.IllegalStateException - if the edge cannot be added at this time due to insertion restrictions

      • getWeight

        W getWeight(V tail,
            V head)
        Returns the weight of the edge from tail to head if the edge exists and has an associated weight, or null otherwise. A null return may also indicate that the weight of the edge was set to null, if the implementation supports null values.
        Parameters:
        tail - the tail vertex
        head - the head vertex
        Returns:
        the weight of the edge from tail to head
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if one or both of the specified elements are null and this graph does not permit null elements

      • setWeight

        W setWeight(V tail,
            V head,
            W weight)
        Sets the weight of the edge from tail to head to the specified weight. Returns the previous weight of the edge if the edge weight was previously set, or null otherwise. A null return may also indicate that the weight of the edge was set to null, if the implementation supports null values.

        If one or both of the specified elements are not in this graph or if an edge from tail to head does not exist, then null is returned.
        Parameters:
        tail - the tail vertex
        head - the head vertex
        weight - the weight of the edge to set
        Returns:
        the previous weight of the edge
        Throws:
        java.lang.NullPointerException - if one or more of the arguments are null and this graph does not permit null values
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if some property of one or more of the arguments prevents the weight of the edge to be set
